RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRANCIPANTS went to the front to an unchallenged pace through the final turn then was challenged down the stretch by outside rival, fended off the challenge and prevailed. NO NANNETTE NO raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch, had traffic entering the final turn, moved out to two wide on that turn then moved inside and slipped through going into the stretch but was empty and was best of the rest. EMBARRASSING was unhurried around the first turn then steadily advanced on the inside down the backstretch, ran into traffic going into the final turn and moved out to two to three path on the final turn, tipped out to five wide in upper stretch to make a late run to improve position. SPENDER was allowed to settle down the backstretch then made a mild two wide bid on the final turn, moved out to six wide in upper stretch but only passed tiring rivals. ZANDREA'S was rank going around the first turn, saved ground throughout but was never a threat. NORTHERN ALLIANCE was off the pace to the middle of the final turn and gave way. CELESTIAL SPIN stalked the pace from three wide down the backstretch then made a mild bid on the final turn but lacked a late response and dropped back.
